Alarko Carrier, Is Bank, Turkcell: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-02-14T07:41:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/alarko-carrier-is-bank-turkcell-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index  rose 308.82, or
0.5 percent, to 64,730.35 on Feb. 11.  Alarko Carrier Sanayii & Ticaret AS (ALCAR TI): The maker
of heating and air conditioning equipment will expand to Iraq in
order to take advantage of a reconstruction-related public
building boom there, it said in an e-mailed statement over the
weekend. Alarko gained 20 kurus, or 0.9 percent, to 22.05 liras.    Turk Ekonomi Bankasi AS  (TEBNK): The bank part-owned by BNP
Paribas SA will complete a merger with  Fortis Bank AS  on Feb.
16, giving 1.0518 shares for each Fortis Bank share, according
to a filing with the Istanbul Stock Exchange today. Turk Ekonomi
fell 5 kurus, or 2.5 percent, to 1.97 liras.    Turkiye Is Bankasi  AS (ISCTR TI): Turkey’s largest listed
bank by assets will publish 2010 full-year results today. Is
Bank, as the lender is known, is expected to report net income
of 2.94 billion liras ($1.9 billion), according to the average
estimate of 28 analysts in a Bloomberg survey. The share rose 4
kurus, or 0.8 percent, to 5.22 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Stockholm-based  TeliaSonera AB , the main shareholder in Turkey’s biggest mobile
phone company with a 37.1 percent stake, will seek to gain
control of the company at an annual general meeting in April,
Milliyet newspaper said two days ago citing TeliaSonera Chief
Executive Officer Lars Nyberg. Turkcell gained 7 kurus, or 0.7
percent, to 10.12 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Bentley at 
 mbentley3@bloomberg.net  